%T A397665 1649631772087,35745880200118,147951368773034,5000564987675006,
%U A397665 20880784275792583,126382307372799276,0,15560236416416655175,137876550371745394142,0,33109718275005955612566
%N A397665 Least integer equal to the sum of the n-th powers of the tens' complements of its digits or 0 if no such number exists.
%C A397665 In other words, least shy n k-digit number, whatever k is.
%C A397665 For any n (exponent) the relation holds: k - log(k) <= n + 1, for k>0. This helps to limit the range of search.
%C A397665 No values for n equal to 4, 11, 18, 21, 24, 25, ...
%e A397665 a(0) = 1 -> (10 - 1)^0 = 9^0 = 1;
%e A397665 a(1) = 5 -> (10 - 5)^1 = 5^1 = 5;
%e A397665 a(2) = 171 -> (10 - 1)^2 + (10 - 7)^2 + (10 - 1)^2 = 9^2 + 3^2 + 9^2 = 81 + 9 + 81 = 171; etc.
%Y A397665 Cf. A003321, A005188, A023052, A261433.
